{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ὅρκος</b>, ὁ, <br /> <b>the object by which one swears,</b> as the Styx among the gods, Στυγὸς ὕδωρ, ὅς τε μέγιστος ὅ. δεινότατός τε πέλει μακάρεσσι θεοῖσι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 15.38, compare 2.755, 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Theogonia” 400, 784, 805, “hymnus ad Cererem” 259, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Metaphysica” 983b31 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; or as Zeus among mortals, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 4.167 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; so of things, ὅρκον δ᾽ ἐνοσφίσθης μέγαν, ἅλας τε καὶ τράπεζαν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 7th c.BC: Archilochus Lyricus 96; οἷς ἦν μέγιστος ὅ... κύων, ἔπειτα χήν 5th c.BC: Cratinus Comicus 231, compare “Placita Philosophorum” 1.3.8: hence, \">Refs 7th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>oath,</b> mostly with epithet μέγας, καρτερός, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus (see. below)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>], etc.; θεῶν ὅ. <b>an oath by</b> the gods, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 2.377; μακάρων ὅ. 10.299, compare 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 647, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 657; ὅ. ἐκ θεῶν μέγας 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 1284; ὅ. κατὰ τῶν.. ὀφθαλμῶν 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator 2.153 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ὅ. πλατύς <b>a</b> firm-based <b>oath,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Empedocles Poeta Philosophus 30.3 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὅρκον ὀμόσαι swear <b>an oath,</b> ὄμοσέν τε τελεύτησέν τε τὸν ὅ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 2.378, etc.; ὅ. ἀπώμνυ [prev. work] 377, compare 10.381; ἐπὶ δ᾽ ὅρκον ὀμεῖται 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Opera et Dies” 194; κατομόσαι 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Taurica” 790 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ὅ. ἐπιορκῆσαι take a false <b>oath,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator 1.115, etc. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; ὅρκου προστεθέντος when <b>an oath</b> is added, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 472, compare “El.” 47 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; δαίμονι τῷ Πλεισθενιδῶν ὅρκους θεμένη having made a <b>sworn compact</b> with.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 1570 (_anapaest meter_); ὅ. ἀλλήλοις ποιοῦνται οἱ μὲν ἔφοροι ὑπὲρ τῆς πόλεως, βασιλεὺς δ᾽ ὑπὲρ ἑαυτοῦ 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Respublica Lacedaemoniorum” 15.7; ὅρκους συνῆψαν 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Phoenissae” 1241, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of the person demanding the oath, ὅ. ἑλέσθαι τινός or τινί take <b>it</b> of him, i.e. make him swear, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 4.746, 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 22.119 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ὅρκους ἐπελάσαι and προσάγειν τινί lay <b>oath</b> upon a man, put him on <b>his oath,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.146, 6.62, 74 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὸν ὅ... ἐπάγειν.. Ὀποντίοις readminister <b>the oath,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Inscriptiones Graecae 9(1).334.12 (_Locrian dialect_, 5th c.BC) \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὅρκους δοὺς καὶ δεξάμενος after tendering <b>his oath</b> to them and accepting theirs, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 6.23, compare “IG” 12.52.18, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 429, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ranae” 589, 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 39.3 and 4; so ὅρκον διδόναι καὶ λαμβάνειν 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Rhetorica” 1377a7, 8 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἀποδοῦναι take <b>it</b> oneself, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 19.318, 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator 3.74 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; ἀπολαμβάνειν administer or tender <b>it,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 5.9, 18.25 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; ὅρκους καὶ πίστιν ἀλλήλοις δότε <b>swear to</b> one another, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Lysistrata” 1185, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 1.107 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὅρκοις καταλαβὼν τὰ τέλη having bound the authorities <b>by oaths,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.86; ὅρκοις κατειλημμένους [prev. author] 1.9 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὅρκῳ ἐμμένειν abide by it, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Medea” 754; ὅ. τηρεῖν 3rd c.AD: Democritus Epigrammaticus 239; παραβαίνειν 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Fragmenta” 286.7, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Aves” 332, 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 19.318; ἐκβάντι τῶν ὅ. 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Symposium” 183b; ἐκλιπεῖν 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Supplices” 1194; συγχέαι [prev. author] “Hipp.” 1063; ἐμπεδοῦν 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 3.2.10: after ὅρκος\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <i>aorist</i>, <i>present</i>, or <i>future</i> <i>infinitive</i> may refer to <i>future</i> time, ὤμοσα καρτερὸν ὅ., μὴ.. ἀναφῆναι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 4.253 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἐμεῦ δ᾽ ἕλετο μέγαν ὅ., μὴ πρὶν σοὶ ἐρέειν[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 746; ὅρκους ἔδοσαν καὶ ἔλαβον, ἀποδοῦναι.., Ἀθηναίους δὲ μὴ πολεμεῖν.. 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 1.3.9: with Preps., οὐκ αὔτως.., ἀλλὰ σὺν ὅρκῳ 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 14.151; σὺν θεῶν ὅρκῳ 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 2.3.12 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; εἶπαι ἐπ᾽ ὅρκου say on <b>oath,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 9.11; κατὰ τοὺς ὅ. 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 5.4.54; opposed to παρ᾽ ὅρκον 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 13.83; παρὰ τοὺς ὅ. 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 2.5.41: proverbial, ὅρκους ἐγὼ γυναικὸς εἰς ὕδωρ γράφω 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 811; parodied by 5th c.BC: Philonides Comicus 7 ὅρκους δὲ μοιχῶν εἰς τέφραν.. γράφω,compare 4th c.BC: Xenarchus Comicus 6, 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus “Μονόστιχοι - Fragmenta Comicorum Graecorum” 25. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> Ὅρκος, personified, son of Eris, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Opera et Dies” 804 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; a divinity who punishes the false and perjured,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 219, “Th.” 231, Oracle texts cited in 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 6.86.γ\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; Διὸς Ὅ., as servant of Zeus, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 1767 (_anapaest meter_). (Cogn. with ἕρκος.) \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G3727","accentedUnicode":"ὅρκος","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G3726","matchingForm":"ὁρκίζω","stepTransliteration":"horkizō","gloss":"to adjure","_zh_tw_Gloss":"懇求 1","_es_Gloss":"suplicar","_zh_Gloss":"恳求 1"},{"strongNumber":"G3728","matchingForm":"ὁρκωμοσία","stepTransliteration":"horkōmosia","gloss":"oath","_zh_tw_Gloss":"起誓","_es_Gloss":"juramento","_zh_Gloss":"起誓"}],"shortDef":"oath","mediumDef":"<b>an oath,</b> <ref='Mat.14.7, 9; 26:72'>Mt. 14:7, 9; 26:72</ref>; <i>metonymy</i> <b>that which is solemnly promised, a vow,</b> <ref='Mat.5.33'>Mt. 5:33</ref>","stepGloss":"oath","stepTransliteration":"horkos","count":10,"_es_Definition":"promesa, juramento","_zh_tw_Definition":"誓言","_zh_Definition":"誓言","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"một lời thề","_zh_tw_Gloss":"誓","_es_Gloss":"juramento","_zh_Gloss":"誓"}]}